### 📊 Variable Reference Examples
##########################################################################

### You can reference the captured responses like this:
### - Document 1 embedding: {{doc1Embedding.response.body.data.0.embedding}}
### - Document 2 embedding: {{doc2Embedding.response.body.data.0.embedding}}
### - Document 3 embedding: {{doc3Embedding.response.body.data.0.embedding}}
### - Query embedding: {{queryEmbedding.response.body.data.0.embedding}}
### - RAG answer: {{ragResponse.response.body.choices.0.message.content}}
### - Security answer: {{securityRagResponse.response.body.choices.0.message.content}}

##########################################################################
### 📊 RAG Workflow Summary
##########################################################################

### This example demonstrated:
### 
### ✅ Document Embedding: Converting text to vector representations using # @name
### ✅ Variable Capture: Using REST Client's # @name syntax for response capture
### ✅ Context Retrieval: Manually selecting relevant documents (simplified for demo)
### ✅ Augmented Generation: Using retrieved context with LLM
### ✅ Conversational RAG: Handling follow-up questions with fresh context
###
### 🎯 Key REST Client Concepts Covered:
### - # @name variableName syntax for response capture
### - {{variableName.response.body.field}} syntax for variable reference
### - Simulating multi-step RAG workflows with variable passing
### - Real-world RAG implementation patterns
###
### 🚀 Production Considerations:
### - Use a proper vector database (Azure AI Search, Pinecone, Weaviate)
### - Implement actual similarity search algorithms
### - Add metadata filtering and hybrid search
### - Optimize embedding models and similarity thresholds
### - Implement caching and performance optimizations
### - Add evaluation metrics for retrieval quality

### 🎓 Try Different Questions:
### - "How can I improve performance of my Azure OpenAI application?"
### - "What are the security best practices for Azure OpenAI?"
### - "How do I monitor costs and usage in Azure OpenAI?"
### - "What should I consider when choosing between GPT models?"

### 💡 Note on Similarity Search:
### In a production RAG system, Step 3 would include:
### 1. Calculate cosine similarity between query and document embeddings
### 2. Rank documents by similarity score
### 3. Select top-k most relevant documents
### 4. Use those as context for generation
### 
### For this REST Client demo, we simplified by manually selecting
### the most relevant documents based on the question topic.
